It's an OK game, but it has several flaws in it. The game skips a lot, especially when you're trying to jump over things or when you're about to destroy a bush. It also skips when you're just running as well. It also causes a great deal of overheating on a tablet. I can only give it 1 star as its flaws are rather serious ones. Fix these problems and I might buy it again and I may even revise my review. Until then, 1 star and I will be requesting a refund for both my husband and myself. Fix the game and you may just get more customers buying this game.         Update: this game has improved somewhat. It doesn't skip or freeze like it did before. Continue improving this and you get more stars.

While the game looks acceptable on my 4.3 inch smartphone, it looks poor on my 9.7 retina display tablet, shame as the videos look much better. Note to developer!, this game really needs a high resolution texture pack I.e same as temple run oz, as potentially this could be a good looking game.  As per other reviews, adverts on a paid game is lame and they pop up frequently.  Flying bits should be really fun but agree with other reviews that control is awful.  Gameplay for running sections really good and perhaps more varied than I.e temple run. Having a mission structure in addition to free runnin adds both variety and longevity.  In a nutshell After Earth could be among the best but in its current state it is simply unfinished, more beta testing I think!

After Earth was the first matinee show I saw in my life, and that is because my school was on fire (summer started early......yay) yet Will and Jaden smith were excellent, but the movie itself was terrible. The app on the other hand is great. It is just another addictive endless running game with a great way to mix temple run and a beat em' up game if you add the little sword swing feature. Overall I enjoy it and glad I bought it. Great job guys :)

There are several issues with control. Occasionally left swipes will be mistaken for a jump. The lag on ducking and jumping is terrible. Flying with any precision is almost impossible. Perhaps something like that is needed here.
